body:
I have an n-bit ripple adder circuit and I have been playing around with the design module because I am new to verilog. However, I upon making a slight modification to the code, icarus is unable to run the simulation and remains hanging. I am wondering why this is a problem. Below is the code. I observed the error is from this line `fulladder ad(cin[i], carryin, cin[25], cin[i+1], sum[i]); `, specifically the presence of `cin[i]` and `cin[i+1]`. Since these are inputs why is the simulator hanging.

```
module fulladder(input logic a, b, carryin, output logic carryout, sum); 
 always @(a, b, carryin) begin 
   sum = a ^ b ^ carryin;
   carryout = a&b | (a^b) & carryin;
 end 
 endmodule

`include "fulladder.sv" 
module rippleadder #(parameter width = 64)(input [width-1:0] a, b, input carryin, output logic carryout, output [width-1:0] sum);
logic [width:0] cin; 
 genvar i; 
always @(*) begin 
 cin[0] =carryin; 
 carryout =cin[width]; 
 end 
generate 
 for(i=0; i<width; i=i+1) begin 
fulladder ad(cin[i], carryin, cin[25], cin[i+1], sum[i]); 
 end 
 endgenerate 
endmodule

```
